The Kiess Syndic Council's institutional monitors have issued a formal interdiction order: the ironpost warden-commander is sustaining dead command authority over the Chalkwind undead from the Archive's sealed wing, and the only way to end his hold on the route zone's dead is direct elimination. The warden-commander is himself an undead officer still running emergency-powers protocols that predate the Ashfall Monsoon. Enter the Archive Sealed Wing and end him.
The warden-commander's emergency-powers protocols have terminated and the Chalkwind undead are no longer receiving command authority from the Archive. Kiess route monitors report that the Saddles wraiths and muster yard ghosts have begun dissipating rather than reconstituting, and the tariff enforcer ghost at the Old Toll Post was found inactive for the first time in recorded observation. The Syndic Council is treating this as confirmation that the Archive's command infrastructure was the binding force for the entire route zone's undead activity.
